          "type": "article_content",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>When we sat down to plan our autumn reset this year, we realised it wasn’t just about cleaning, it was about making the house feel ready for the season. Here’s what we do together:</p><p><strong>1. Clear and clean</strong></p><ul><li>We both declutter the house first, then blitz surfaces with Purdy & Figg.</li></ul><p><strong>2. Cosy lighting</strong></p><ul><li>Tom’s big on swapping out bright bulbs for warm lamps for an instant mood shift.</li></ul><p><strong>3. Layering textures</strong></p><ul><li>drag out the chunky knits and throws (Tom pretends not to care, but always ends up wrapped in one).</li></ul><p><strong>4. Bringing outdoors in</strong></p><ul><li>We both love houseplants, so we always add to our collection when the temperature dips.</li></ul><p><strong>5. Switch up scents</strong></p><ul><li>Candle, diffusers and Purdy & Figg’s gorgeous Ginger & Citrus scent create the perfect autumn vibe.</li></ul>"
          }
        },
